Rating: 4
Really good tart and relatively easy! I used whole wheat pastry flour for the crust, and substituted goat milk yogurt for the sour cream, and cut down on the butter by adding less to the polenta mixture. I also added sliced zucchini and red onion to the mushrooms. Also, let the tart sit after baking for a least a half hour, it will help the polenta set firmly. More veggies are definitely a plus! My fiance loved it!

Rating: 4
This is one of the best tarts I have ever made! I made my own whole spelt crust and forgot to add the butter to the polenta mixture (a VERY good mishap). The dish most definitely had a WOW factor. Used 3/4 of a cup of dry polenta and made it in the microwave with about 2 1/2 cups of instant vegetable broth, which was plenty of liquid

Rating: 3
I was also confused about how much polenta to use. I made the recipe and used 1 cup of polenta. The flavor was excellent, but the tart never set properly. I think I will use 3 cups next time and see what happens.

