Rating: 4
Yummy, yummy, yummy! I've made this recipe a few times, each time with a slight variation. So far, the best additions are chopped sundried tomatoes and roasted red peppers added to the mushroom mixture. A little rosemary is a nice change too. As for the pie crust, Pillsbury ready made crust works well.

Rating: 4
Fabulous recipe. I did it in a 9" round tart pan and used a mix of white, shitake, and dried mushrooms, and added shallots for a little more flavor. It came out great, although I might use even more mushrooms next time. I put the polenta and goat cheese through my food mill, much easier than forcing through a sieve or grater. I served it as a side dish with lamb chops and it got raves.

