I loved this recipe. I subsituted cream cheese for the goat cheese and it still turned out great!

Rating: 4
This was fabulous. I took many shortcuts: used Nancy's frozen piecrust (yummy), blended the filling in the cuisinart (except for the mushrooms), came out great and was much easier than the sieve method.

Rating: 4
This has become one of our regular dinner menus for my husband and myself. We cheat a little by using the prepared pie crust that you roll out. We usually warm half of it for another dinner and, granted it's not as good, but it's still good enough. I am planning to make this for a small group of ladies coming over next week along with a green salad and brownies for dessert.

